        </exercise>
    </exercises>
    <axiom component="lesson-plan">
        <title>Differentiation Strategies</title>
        <p xml:id="auto_gn8w5fdc">
            <alert>For Struggling Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_hfg0kgf1">
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_e5d1qm3p"><p xml:id="auto_peh0kwzh">Provide pre-drawn shapes with labelled vertices.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_ms8vmrow"><p xml:id="auto_3r0tm8db">Use colour coding: one colour for original, another for translated shape.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_5vexmzlt"><p xml:id="auto_mmwepwtf">Provide step-by-step calculation templates.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_5rz9s1ap"><p xml:id="auto_x0bo7hk1">Start with simple translations (positive integers only).</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_mq4pyuee"><p xml:id="auto_5ls6e229">Use physical manipulatives (cut-out shapes) to show sliding.</p></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_8czdtzz9">
            <alert>For On-Level Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_k1b7utx1">
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_i8umv8yl"><p xml:id="auto_elmomazw">Encourage students to create their own translation problems.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_1u3qzrnz"><p xml:id="auto_tclqdjyk">Ask students to explain why translation preserves congruence.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_830t9upg"><p xml:id="auto_ievmokpr">Provide mixed practice with positive and negative translations.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_jnyncp9t"><p xml:id="auto_qdcuqjl4">Challenge students to find inverse translations.</p></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_6e6f0dei">
            <alert>For Advanced Learners:</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_dy43czsp">
            <ul>
                <li xml:id="auto_qqg9t1g5"><p xml:id="auto_ikqrrltf">Explore composition of translations (two translations in sequence).</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_ctkx458t"><p xml:id="auto_mwgwofxd">Investigate translations in three dimensions.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_gm5w6m59"><p xml:id="auto_2og46zf9">Challenge: Prove that translation preserves distance and angle.</p></li>
                <li xml:id="auto_0lho6m1o"><p xml:id="auto_dvb470mu">Explore applications in computer graphics (sprite movement in games).</p></li>
            </ul>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_msk7gqch">
            <alert>Extension Activity: Animation and Computer Graphics</alert>
        </p>
        <p xml:id="auto_k3nihav9">
            Work in pairs. Design a simple animation where a character moves across the screen using three translation vectors. Calculate the resultant single translation vector that maps the character from its starting position to its final position directly.
        </p>
    </axiom>
